{"title":"Barding (item)","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Barding_(item)","type":"markdown","data":"| (           |                                   |\n| ----------- | --------------------------------- |\n| Name        | barding                           |\n| Appearance  | barding                           |\n| Base price  | 300 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") |\n| Weight      | [250](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")      |\n| Material    | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\")         |\n| Monster use | *Will not be used by monsters.*   |\n\n**Barding** is a type of [tool](/wiki/Tool \"Tool\") that appears in [EvilHack](/wiki/EvilHack \"EvilHack\") and [Hack'EM](/wiki/Hack%27EM \"Hack'EM\"). It is a set of [barding](/wiki/Barding \"Barding\") that has a base [object material](/wiki/Object_materials_\\(EvilHack\\) \"Object materials (EvilHack)\") of [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\").\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Generation](#Generation)\n- [2 Description](#Description)\n- [3 Strategy](#Strategy)\n- [4 Encyclopedia entry](#Encyclopedia_entry)\n\n## Generation\n\nA monster that is [generated with](/wiki/Monster_starting_inventory \"Monster starting inventory\") a [saddle](/wiki/Saddle \"Saddle\") has an effective 3⁄400 chance (0.75%) of generating with a set of standard barding.\n\nGeneral [stores](/wiki/Store \"Store\") and hardware stores can sell barding.\n\nBarding can be created at a [forge](/wiki/Forge_\\(dungeon_feature\\) \"Forge (dungeon feature)\") by combining [plate mail](/wiki/Plate_mail \"Plate mail\") and a saddle.\n\n## Description\n\nA [hero](/wiki/Hero \"Hero\") can [apply](/wiki/Apply \"Apply\") barding to a [pet](/wiki/Pet \"Pet\") that is eligible for [riding](/wiki/Riding \"Riding\") to equip them with it, though they can resist as with an applied saddle - the hero can enchant their steed's barding by reading a [scroll of enchant armor](/wiki/Scroll_of_enchant_armor \"Scroll of enchant armor\") while mounted on the steed; a prompt will appear to confirm whether or not the steed's barding is the intended target.\n\nWhile worn, barding grants 3 base [AC](/wiki/AC \"AC\").\n\n## Strategy\n\nThough it is the most basic of its item type, barding offers an additional level of survivability to a steed by increasing its AC, and the head coverage makes it less likely to be felled by the [illness](/wiki/Illness \"Illness\")-inducing bite of a [zombie](/wiki/Zombie_\\(EvilHack\\) \"Zombie (EvilHack)\").\n\n## Encyclopedia entry\n\nBarding (also spelled bard or barb) is body armour for war horses.  \nThe practice of armoring horses was first extensively developed in  \nantiquity in the eastern kingdoms of Parthia and Pahlava, and  \nafter the conquests of Alexander the Great it made its way into  \nEuropean military practices via the Seleucid Empire and later  \nByzantine Empire. Though its historical roots lie in antiquity in  \nthe regions of what was once the Persian Empire, barded horses have  \nbecome a symbol of the late European Middle Ages chivalry and the  \nera of knights.  \n\\[ Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia ]\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Barding (item) - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Barding_(item)\",\"wgTitle\":\"Barding (item)\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":175668,\"wgRevisionId\":175668,\"wgArticleId\":38822,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Encyclopedia\",\"EvilHack tools\",\"Hack'EM tools\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"w