=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Barding is a type of tool that appears in EvilHack and Hack&#039;EM. It is a set of barding that has a base object material of iron.\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/Barding_(item)\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Barding_item rootpage-Barding_item skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Barding (item)</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<table class=\"prettytable\" style=\"margin: 0;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><span class=\"nhsym clr-cyan\">(</span>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Name\n</th>\n<td>barding\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Appearance\n</th>\n<td>barding\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Base price\n</th>\n<td>300 <a href=\"/wiki/Zorkmid\" title=\"Zorkmid\">zm</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weight\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Weight\" title=\"Weight\">250</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Material\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Monster use\n</th>\n<td><small><i>Will not be used by monsters.</i></small>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>\n<p><b>Barding</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Tool\" title=\"Tool\">tool</a> that appears in <a href=\"/wiki/EvilHack\" title=\"EvilHack\">EvilHack</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Hack%27EM\" title=\"Hack&#39;EM\">Hack'EM</a>. It is a set of <a href=\"/wiki/Barding\" title=\"Barding\">barding</a> that has a base <a href=\"/wiki/Object_materials_(EvilHack)\" title=\"Object materials (EvilHack)\">object material</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Generation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Generation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Strategy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Strategy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Encyclopedia_entry\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Encyclopedia entry</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Generation\">Generation</span></h2>\n<p>A monster that is <a href=\"/wiki/Monster_starting_inventory\" title=\"Monster starting inventory\">generated with</a> a <a href=\"/wiki/Saddle\" title=\"Saddle\">saddle</a> has an effective <sup>3</sup>&#8260;<sub>400</sub> chance (0.75%) of generating with a set of standard barding.\n</p><p>General <a href=\"/wiki/Store\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Store\">stores</a> and hardware stores can sell barding.\n</p><p>Barding can be created at a <a href=\"/wiki/Forge_(dungeon_feature)\" title=\"Forge (dungeon feature)\">forge</a> by combining <a href=\"/wiki/Plate_mail\" title=\"Plate mail\">plate mail</a> and a saddle.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span></h2>\n<p>A <a href=\"/wiki/Hero\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hero\">hero</a> can <a href=\"/wiki/Apply\" title=\"Apply\">apply</a> barding to a <a href=\"/wiki/Pet\" title=\"Pet\">pet</a> that is eligible for <a href=\"/wiki/Riding\" title=\"Riding\">riding</a> to equip them with it, though they can resist as with an applied saddle - the hero can enchant their steed's barding by reading a <a href=\"/wiki/Scroll_of_enchant_armor\" title=\"Scroll of enchant armor\">scroll of enchant armor</a> while mounted on the steed; a prompt will appear to confirm whether or not the steed's barding is the intended target.\n</p><p>While worn, barding grants 3 base <a href=\"/wiki/AC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"AC\">AC</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>Though it is the most basic of its item type, barding offers an additional level of survivability to a steed by increasing its AC, and the head coverage makes it less likely to be felled by the <a href=\"/wiki/Illness\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Illness\">illness</a>-inducing bite of a <a href=\"/wiki/Zombie_(EvilHack)\" title=\"Zombie (EvilHack)\">zombie</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Encyclopedia_entry\">Encyclopedia entry</span></h2><div class=\"nhencyclopedia\">\n<div class=\"poem\">\n<p>Barding (also spelled bard or barb) is body armour for war horses.<br />\n\tThe practice of armoring horses was first extensively developed in<br />\n\tantiquity in the eastern kingdoms of Parthia and Pahlava, and<br />\n\tafter the conquests of Alexander the Great it made its way into<br />\n\tEuropean military practices via the Seleucid Empire and later<br />\n\tByzantine Empire.  Though its historical roots lie in antiquity in<br />\n\tthe regions of what was once the Persian Empire, barded horses have<br />\n\tbecome a symbol of the late European Middle Ages chivalry and the<br />\n\tera of knights.<br />\n\t\t[ Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia ]<br />\n</p>\n<div style=\"text-align:right\"> </div>\n</div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926182517\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.015 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.054 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 84/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 537/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1291/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 633/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 969/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   23.612      1 -total\n 47.59%   11.238      1 Template:Tool\n 41.14%    9.713      1 Template:Encyclopedia\n 32.74%    7.730      1 Template:Metal_color\n 21.61%    5.103      1 Template:Cyan\n 10.38%    2.450      1 Template:Frac\n  9.43%    2.226      1 Template:Right-align\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wikihackdb:pcache:idhash:38822-0!canonical and timestamp 20240926182517 and revision id 175668\n -->\n</div></div>\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"printfooter\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\tRetrieved from \"<a dir=\"ltr\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?title=Barding_(item)&amp;oldid=175668\">https://nethackwiki.com/index.php?t